Or should I cook for you here?

00:35:59.260 --> 00:36:00.410
I’m too lazy to go out.

00:36:01.840 --> 00:36:03.440
I was planning to make ranjuan curry.

00:36:04.010 --> 00:36:05.330
to offer to my mom tomorrow morning.

00:36:06.700 --> 00:36:07.720
Ranjuan curry?

00:36:08.690 --> 00:36:10.000
I’ve heard of it,

00:36:11.330 --> 00:36:13.330
but never tried it.

00:36:14.210 --> 00:36:14.910
Then…

00:36:16.460 --> 00:36:17.770
I’ll cook it for you.

00:36:19.410 --> 00:36:20.200
Sure.

00:36:23.900 --> 00:36:25.040
Well…

00:36:25.040 --> 00:36:25.540
Inn.

00:36:33.250 --> 00:36:33.980
Yes?

00:36:34.520 --> 00:36:36.810
Go buy the ingredients for Po.

00:36:37.290 --> 00:36:39.250
I'm good, you don't need to do that.

00:36:39.250 --> 00:36:40.290
I've got this for you

00:36:40.600 --> 00:36:42.230
Just let Inn buy them

00:36:42.570 --> 00:36:43.500
Alright.

00:36:45.490 --> 00:36:46.580
Well then,

00:36:53.730 --> 00:36:54.230
Inn

00:36:55.200 --> 00:36:56.470
take this with you.

00:36:59.340 --> 00:37:01.340
Are you my fan or something?

00:37:01.830 --> 00:37:02.390
Come on,

00:37:02.390 --> 00:37:03.630
I’ll sign it for you.

00:37:07.090 --> 00:37:07.590
No

00:37:08.140 --> 00:37:08.980
you don’t have to.

00:37:09.760 --> 00:37:11.470
Hey, let me sign it.

00:37:12.150 --> 00:37:13.450
Inn, go already.

00:37:13.450 --> 00:37:14.240
Yes.

00:37:17.400 --> 00:37:18.590
I’ll sign it for you.

00:37:18.590 --> 00:37:19.430
Sasom!

00:37:20.310 --> 00:37:21.040
Are you teasing me?

00:37:21.040 --> 00:37:22.310
Hey, that hurts.

00:37:22.790 --> 00:37:24.790
Stop, I’ll really sign it.

00:37:25.330 --> 00:37:26.740
I’ll pull your ears out.

00:37:27.030 --> 00:37:27.530
Hey, you!

00:37:28.690 --> 00:37:30.690
Are you teasing me?

00:37:31.030 --> 00:37:32.220
That hurts.

00:37:32.220 --> 00:37:33.340
Are you being stubborn?

00:37:33.340 --> 00:37:34.710
I have a shoot tomorrow.

00:37:34.710 --> 00:37:36.520
If my ears turn red,

00:37:36.520 --> 00:37:38.520
I won’t be able to work.

00:37:38.810 --> 00:37:40.630
Then don’t go. Stay with me.

00:37:40.870 --> 00:37:42.250
I can’t.

00:37:53.930 --> 00:37:55.110
Can you help scoop this for me?

00:37:56.820 --> 00:37:57.700
Sure.

00:38:10.370 --> 00:38:11.550
Smells good, right?

00:38:11.940 --> 00:38:13.070
It smells amazing.

00:38:15.890 --> 00:38:16.770
Like this.

00:38:31.240 --> 00:38:34.600
Can you help chop this?

00:38:40.240 --> 00:38:41.040
Is this it?

00:38:57.800 --> 00:38:59.170
Do you like cooking?

00:39:02.430 --> 00:39:03.290
Me?

00:39:08.500 --> 00:39:10.000
Not really.

00:39:11.220 --> 00:39:13.250
I prefer being an assistant.

00:39:20.580 --> 00:39:21.080
When I was a kid,

00:39:22.060 --> 00:39:23.870
I liked helping my governess.

00:39:26.340 --> 00:39:26.840
Your governess?

00:39:27.340 --> 00:39:30.000
The woman who raised me and Ngern.

00:39:31.610 --> 00:39:32.910
Oh.

00:39:33.940 --> 00:39:35.580
What’s next?

00:39:35.820 --> 00:39:36.670
Once that’s done,

00:39:37.110 --> 00:39:39.730
put those leaves into the pot.

00:39:40.000 --> 00:39:41.090
As for the rest,

00:39:41.870 --> 00:39:43.090
I think…

00:39:43.090 --> 00:39:46.150
just seasoning a bit should do it.

00:39:48.390 --> 00:39:50.000
You sound so knowledgeable.

00:39:51.900 --> 00:39:54.760
I don’t know anything about this.

00:39:55.370 --> 00:39:56.350
Not really.

00:39:56.830 --> 00:39:58.840
I just remember it from my grandma.

00:39:59.800 --> 00:40:01.590
I might be remembering it wrong.

00:40:43.530 --> 00:40:44.420
Would you please…

00:40:44.420 --> 00:40:45.400
Try tasting it.

00:40:48.030 --> 00:40:48.850
Isn’t it sinful

00:40:49.390 --> 00:40:50.260
to eat food meant for offerings?

00:40:51.090 --> 00:40:52.410
It’s not.

00:40:52.950 --> 00:40:54.500
I made a small pot just for you.

00:40:54.500 --> 00:40:55.530
The big pot

00:40:56.160 --> 00:40:57.770
is for offerings tomorrow morning.

00:41:01.610 --> 00:41:02.920
Try it.

00:41:05.940 --> 00:41:06.740
Rangjuan curry.

00:41:07.710 --> 00:41:09.180
It’s fragrant, just like the name.

00:41:33.900 --> 00:41:35.270
This is insanely good.

00:41:37.020 --> 00:41:38.510
Seriously,

00:41:38.510 --> 00:41:41.720
is there any country where you can marry curry?

00:41:42.770 --> 00:41:43.980
What did you say?

00:41:45.540 --> 00:41:47.910
I want to marry your curry.

00:41:49.080 --> 00:41:50.000
I’ll eat it every day.

00:41:52.280 --> 00:41:54.420
Why marry curry?

00:41:54.900 --> 00:41:55.850
Let me do…

00:41:56.340 --> 00:41:58.260
the cooking for you every day instead

00:42:00.260 --> 00:42:00.830
That’s true.

00:42:02.340 --> 00:42:05.510
Then I’ll marry the cook instead.

00:42:20.240 --> 00:42:21.530
You…

00:43:48.110 --> 00:43:48.960
Hey…

00:43:50.390 --> 00:43:52.530
Why did you come so late?

00:43:52.920 --> 00:43:54.210
The shop’s about to close.

00:43:54.650 --> 00:43:56.900
I wanted to see if you were tired today.

00:44:02.400 --> 00:44:03.670
And…

00:44:06.630 --> 00:44:08.610
I’m not very good at flirting,

00:44:09.390 --> 00:44:10.870
but when I’m with you,

00:44:11.500 --> 00:44:12.850
I feel at ease.

00:44:16.170 --> 00:44:17.900
You’re funny,

00:44:19.250 --> 00:44:20.790
but you seem sincere.

00:45:16.980 --> 00:45:18.400
Try drinking this.

00:45:18.400 --> 00:45:20.540
It might help you sleep.

00:45:51.060 --> 00:45:53.940
I never thought I’d like men,

00:45:56.270 --> 00:45:57.390
but with you,

00:45:58.270 --> 00:46:00.000
I can’t resist.

00:46:03.540 --> 00:46:05.340
Then don’t resist.

00:46:06.020 --> 00:46:07.130
Because I feel...

00:46:07.670 --> 00:46:08.870
the same way

00:48:22.110 --> 00:48:23.270
Slowly.

00:48:30.230 --> 00:48:31.390
Thank you.

